-- Egypt Agrees to Buy 180,000 Metric Tons of Wheat From Russia, Nomani Says
-- Ola Galal
-- 2010-07-31T14:45:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-31/egypt-agrees-to-buy-180-000-metric-ton-of-wheat-from-russia-nomani-says.html

          
          
             Egypt agreed to buy 180,000 metric
tons of wheat from Russia, Nomani Nomani, vice chairman of the
General Authority for Supply Commodities said in Cairo today.  
 Egypt will buy 60,000 tons from Bunge Ltd. at $239.50 per
ton, 60,000 tons from Cargill Inc. at $238 per ton, and a
further 60,000 tons from Cargill at $243 per ton.  
